\f0\b\fs44 \cf0 Directions\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl400\sa140\ql\qnatural

\f1\b0\fs42 \cf0 Completely melt the chocolate in a {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/double-boiler/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 double boiler}}. Add the cream to a medium bowl and pour in the chocolate. Whisk the mixture very slowly creating a shiny, elastic {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/emulsion/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 emulsion}}.\
Whisk in the butter, then add the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/liqueur/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 liqueur}}, to taste, until well combined.\
Pour the mixture into a fondue pot. Dip your choice of bites into the fondue using fondue forks and enjoy!\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl320\ql\qnatural

